                subtype="historical-document" type="document" xml:id="d200">
                <note rend="inline" type="source">793.94/13328: Telegram</note>
                <head>
                    <hi rend="italic">The <gloss type="from">Secretary of State</gloss> to the
                        Ambassador in Japan</hi> (<persName type="to">
                        <hi rend="italic">Grew</hi>
                    </persName>)</head>
                <opener>
                    <dateline rendition="#right">
                        <placeName>
                            <hi rend="smallcaps">Washington</hi>
                        </placeName>, <date calendar="gregorian" when="1938-06-29T19:00:00-04:00"
                            >June 29, 1938—7 p.m.</date>
                    </dateline>
                </opener>
                <p>222. Your 423, June 28, 8 p.m., first paragraph. Press despatches from London,
                    under date June 27, indicate that the British and French have reached an
                    understanding on the issue under reference. Quotation from the press is being
                    sent in a separate telegram via Shanghai.<note n="83" xml:id="d200fn83">See <hi
                            rend="italic">supra</hi>.</note>
                </p>
                <closer>
                    <signed>
                        <hi rend="smallcaps">Hull</hi>
                    </signed>
                </closer>
            </div>
        </body>
    </text>
